oop review rule is already established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level safety result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that containment-first version safety is established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level isolation result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that mailbox state stays isolated from legacy board/tab metadata, so rollback remains straightforward.\n- Keep the rule-level opt-in result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that team-mode surfaces remain additive and secondary, not replacements for existing single-thread flows.\n- Keep the rule-level non-regression result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that current mailbox work has stayed non-destructive across thread lifecycle, board interaction, auto-continue, and loop-control surfaces.\n- Keep the rule-layer cleanup result fixed: for the current mailbox scope, rule-level process and safety debt is effectively closed; remaining unresolved work is execution hardening plus later delivery hygiene.\n- Keep the analysis-convergence result fixed: further analysis-only repo edits are no longer justified unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the post-convergence result fixed: repeated analysis after convergence has not surfaced any new regression, so the remaining critical-path work is still the Task 6 resolver slice.\n- Keep the audit freeze fixed: further analysis passes should not change the resolver execution target unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the resolver spec fixed: no further analysis narrowing is needed beyond `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads` unless a real regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the remaining-gap result fixed: with no containment trigger in the current review window, the only unresolved Task 6 work is the live-thread resolver pair plus the syntax-check step that follows the future code change.\n- Keep the next pass hardening-first: execute the remaining Task 6 stale-thread validation work in `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md` by adding one shared live-thread resolver in `src/host/team-coordination.js`, sourcing it from `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads`, and using it only in `assignTaskToThread`, `claimTaskForThread`, `heartbeatThread`, `blockTaskForThread`, and `completeTaskForThread`.\n- Keep the execution boundary fixed: do not expand that slice into mailbox UI changes, stale-lease recovery, or broader supervisor flow changes.\n- Keep the closure rule fixed: the resolver slice should close both Task 6 thread-validation checkboxes together, because the resolver is the concrete implementation of the stale-thread rejection outcome.\n- If the hardening pass finds risk to current stable behavior, pause feature expansion and route the following pass to containment or rollback-friendly isolation.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
